<section class="wa-section--bleed" aria-labelledby="wa-manifesto-page-title" style="position:relative; overflow:hidden;">
  <div class="wa-aurora" aria-hidden="true"><div class="wa-aurora__blob"></div></div>
  <div class="wa-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <article class="wa-prose" style="position:relative; z-index:2;">
    <span class="wa-eyebrow">Manifesto</span>
    <h1 id="wa-manifesto-page-title" style="margin-top: var(--wa-space-4);">
      Software you buy. <span class="wa-gradient-text">Once.</span>
    </h1>

    <p>
      Somewhere along the way, software ate the world вЂ” and then started charging
      rent on the bite marks. Every workflow turned into a subscription. Every
      tool became a tenant in your bank account. And every operator, marketer,
      and trader started paying $9, $29, $99 a month for the privilege of
      doing their own job.
    </p>

    <p>We think that&rsquo;s weird.</p>

    <h2>What we make</h2>
    <p>
      Desktop tools. Real binaries that live on your hard drive. They start when
      you double-click them and stop when you close them. No login screens. No
      <em>oops, our cloud is down today</em>. No telemetry pinging some growth
      team in San Francisco about how often you press <strong>Ctrl+S</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>Who they&rsquo;re for</h2>
    <p>
      People who already know what they&rsquo;re doing. CRM operators who push
      ten campaigns a week. Traders staring at six exchange tabs. Marketers
      who write better than the AI. Anyone whose workflow is too specific for
      a SaaS dashboard built by people who&rsquo;ve never done the work.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don&rsquo;t do</h2>
    <p>
      No subscriptions. No cloud sync. No <em>seats</em>. No usage limits. No
      AI features bolted on so the deck looks fundable. No license server that
      can brick your tool when our domain expires. No analytics on your
      keystrokes.
    </p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>
      You buy the tool once. You download the installer. You run it for the
      next decade if you want. When we ship a major update, you get it free
      for one year, then you decide if v2 is worth another payment. Open file
      formats вЂ” your data is yours, in plain JSON or CSV, the day you stop
      using us.
    </p>

    <h2>The deal</h2>
    <p>
      We make the tool. You pay once. We don&rsquo;t hassle you again. If the
      company ever folds, the tool keeps working. If you ever want a refund,
      ask within 30 days, no questions, no exit-survey form.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top: var(--wa-space-12);">
      <strong>Built once. Yours forever.</strong>
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top: var(--wa-space-10); display:flex; gap: var(--wa-space-3); flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <a href="{{ routes.collections_url }}/all" class="wa-button-primary">Browse the tools</a>
      <a href="/pages/contact#request" class="wa-button-ghost">Request something new</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "WA Manifesto Page",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "wa-section--bleed",
  "settings": [],
  "presets": [{ "name": "WA Manifesto Page" }]
}
{% endschema %}
